- Backend: `mbam-api/src/bin/auth_switch.rs` was a stale, never-finished debug CLI (menu options mostly printed "Pending implementation" text, including for OAuth flows that were later actually built for real in `modules/auth/routes.rs` — the tool never caught up). Deleted it, and deleted `mbam-api/docs/API_DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md`, which documented an abandoned "every feature needs a terminal switch runner" convention — only `auth_switch` was ever built despite the doc listing `transaction_switch`/`product_switch`/`pending_payment_switch` as required, and `checklist_tests.rs`'s real integration tests are what actually verify backend behavior today. Removed the matching "Terminal switch testing rule" sections from `mbam-api/docs/AUTHENTICATION_DESIGN.md` and `mbam-api/README_MAC_DEBUG.md` (renumbering the latter's remaining steps). This was a standalone `[[bin]]` (Cargo auto-discovers `src/bin/*.rs`) with zero callers from the library crate or `checklist_tests.rs`, so removing it carries no risk to the running API or the test suite.
- Frontend: `components/auth/LoginForm.tsx`, `SignupForm.tsx`, `SSOButtons.tsx`, and the `icons.tsx` they exclusively imported were dead — confirmed via `grep` that none of the four files were referenced anywhere outside themselves. `AuthPage.tsx` (the only screen that renders `AuthLayout` for sign-in) exclusively uses `loginWithKeycloak()`/`recoverKeycloakAccount()` plus an offline-passphrase unlock; it never renders these components. They were the in-app login/signup forms from before the frontend fully moved to Keycloak-hosted sign-in, left behind after that migration. Deleted all four files.
