Change: Extended the raw transaction/line-item detail report (mbam-api's `reports::service::transaction_detail`, Master Owner/Business Admin only) to filter by *multiple* businesses, shops, employees, and products at once, per the user's request to "click on employees and then details ... use a search box to build the report for a particular employee or set of employees same for the shops and order parametres already present on the page", with a "," delimiter for grouping multiple selections.
Investigation: The endpoint already accepted one optional id per dimension (`ReportQuery.business_id`/`business_unit_id`/`employee_id`/`product_id`, each `Option<Uuid>`). Needed a distinct query type and repository filter shape that accept a list per dimension without disturbing the existing single-id aggregate dimension reports (`business_revenue`/`shop_revenue`/`employee_sales`/`product_sales`), which stay single-entity chart views.
Implementation (backend): Added `ReportDetailQuery` (model.rs) with `business_ids`/`business_unit_ids`/`employee_ids`/`product_ids: Option<String>` (comma-separated). Changed repository `DetailFilters` fields from `Option<Uuid>` to `Vec<Uuid>` and its SQL filter clauses from `($N::uuid is null or col = $N)` to `($N::uuid[] = array[]::uuid[] or col = any($N))` (empty vec = no restriction, matching the existing `ReportScope.business_unit_ids` convention). Refactored `service.rs`: extracted `report_window`'s body into a primitive-argument `build_report_window(timeframe, timezone, start_date, end_date: Option<&str>)` shared by both `report_window` (ReportQuery) and the new `report_detail_window` (ReportDetailQuery), so timeframe/custom-range parsing isn't duplicated; generalized `validate_requested_business_scope` from two `Option<Uuid>` params to `impl IntoIterator<Item = Uuid>` for both params (an `Option<Uuid>` already implements this, so the existing single-id call site needed no change); added `parse_uuid_list(Option<&str>) -> Result<Vec<Uuid>, ApiError>` for comma-separated parsing (blank entries between commas ignored, any non-empty malformed entry returns 400); rewrote `transaction_detail` to parse all four id lists, validate business/unit ids against the caller's scope (fail-closed 404 on any id outside scope, same as the single-id path), and changed both `record_authorization_event` calls' structured `business_id`/`business_unit_id` columns to `None` (multiple ids no longer fit a single-UUID column) with the actual lists moved into the `metadata` JSON instead. Updated `routes.rs`'s `transaction_detail` handler to extract `Query<ReportDetailQuery>`.
Implementation (frontend): Added `mbam-web/src/services/entityDirectoryService.ts` — a shared `loadEntityItems(kind)` covering all four dimensions (`businesses` now added via `loadAuthorizationBootstrap().businesses`, alongside the pre-existing shops/employees/products logic moved out of `EntityReportDetailPage.tsx` unchanged). Added `components/reports/EntityMultiSelect.tsx` — search box + removable tag list per dimension, backed by `loadEntityItems`. Added `ReportDetailFilters` (reportService.ts) alongside the existing single-id `ReportFilters`, with `loadReportTransactionDetail` switched to it and a new `detailQuery()` joining each id array with `,`. `ReportsPage.tsx`: un-hid the dimension tabs so they render in both Summary and Detail view (previously `{view === "summary" && (...)}`), added per-dimension selection state (`selectedIdsByDimension: Record<ReportDimension, string[]>`) so switching tabs doesn't clear a different dimension's picks, rendered `EntityMultiSelect` for the active dimension only in Detail view, and built `detailFilters` (only the active dimension's selected ids feed the request, matching "click on employees and then details" — one active picker/filter at a time). `ReportDetailTable.tsx` switched its `filters` prop to `ReportDetailFilters` and its effect's dependency array to `businessIdsKey`/etc. (each a plain `.join(",")`-derived variable, not an inline expression, to keep `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps` static-checkable).
Files changed: `mbam-api/src/modules/reports/model.rs`, `repository.rs`, `service.rs`, `routes.rs`; `mbam-api/src/checklist_tests.rs`; `mbam-web/src/services/entityDirectoryService.ts` (new), `reportService.ts`; `mbam-web/src/components/reports/EntityMultiSelect.tsx` + `.css` (new); `mbam-web/src/pages/reports/ReportsPage.tsx` + `.css`, `ReportDetailTable.tsx`, `EntityReportDetailPage.tsx`; `mbam-web/src/i18n/reportsPageResources.ts`; `debug.log`, `docs/ENGINEERING_DEBUG_LOG.md`.
Verification: Backend — no Rust toolchain in this sandbox (unchanged constraint from earlier sessions); reviewed every changed function by re-reading the full file after each edit, confirmed positional `.bind()` calls match the SQL's `$N` order, confirmed `Option<Uuid>` satisfies `IntoIterator<Item = Uuid>` so the existing single-id `validate_requested_scope` call site needed no change, and added `transaction_detail_report_supports_multi_entity_filters` to `checklist_tests.rs` (multi-employee union, single-employee-of-multi narrowing, multi-shop union, a multi-id request containing one cross-tenant shop id fail-closed to 404, a malformed id anywhere in a comma list returning 400, multi-product union) alongside the pre-existing `transaction_detail_report_is_role_gated_and_scoped` — both need the user's local `cargo test` to actually execute, per this repo's sandbox constraint. Frontend — `npx tsc --noEmit` clean, `npx eslint` clean (0 errors/warnings after extracting the join()-derived dependency variables), `npx vitest run` passed (21 files / 58 tests, unchanged — `ReportsPage.test.tsx`'s three tests never exercise Detail view so were unaffected by un-hiding the tabs or the new picker; `EntityReportDetailPage.test.tsx` continued to pass unmodified because its `vi.mock` targets are the same `authorizationService`/`teamService`/`productService` module paths that `entityDirectoryService.ts` now wraps), `npm run build` succeeded.
