Investigation: Traced the actual click-to-print flow in `TransactionRecordPage.tsx`/`TransactionInvoicePage.tsx` and confirmed it was already correctly wired (print button has `data-intent="print"`, `handleSubmit` reads `event.nativeEvent.submitter`, navigates to `/transactions/:id/invoice?print=1`, and the invoice page's effect calls `window.print()` after a 250ms delay when `print=1` is present) — so the reported bug was not a broken handler. Asked the user what they actually see; they said the print button "appears to be turned off." Grepped every CSS file in `mbam-web` (18 files, plus the compiled `dist` bundle) for `.primary-btn`/`.secondary-btn`/`.form-actions` and found **zero** rules anywhere in the app — these classes are used throughout the codebase (invoice page, reports, team, business pages, this record page) but have no base styling at all; only `.record-sale-btn` has its own explicit green color overrides (still no padding/border-radius/base look, those are equally undefined). So every "Save draft"/"Print invoice" button in the app renders as a bare, unstyled native `<button>` — flat gray system chrome next to the one deliberately-colored green "Record sale" button, which reads as "off" by contrast even though it's fully clickable.
Implementation: Scoped the fix to this page only (not a global `.primary-btn`/`.secondary-btn` styling pass, to avoid unreviewed side effects on every other page sharing those class names). In `TransactionRecordPage.tsx`: added three small dependency-free inline SVG icon components (`SaveDraftIcon`, `RecordSaleIcon`, `PrintInvoiceIcon` — floppy disk, checkmark circle, printer; all `aria-hidden` since each button already has a visible text label) and wired one into each of the three `.form-actions` buttons, plus a shared `.form-action-btn` class and a `.print-invoice-btn` class on the print button (previously bare `.primary-btn`, i.e. functionally identical to the invisible base case above). In `TransactionRecordPage.css`: added `.form-actions` flex-row layout, a `.form-action-btn` base pill style (padding/border-radius/font-weight/icon sizing/hover-active transitions), `.form-actions .secondary-btn` colors (white/bordered) for Save draft, and `.print-invoice-btn` colors (solid `var(--forest)`, matching the app's primary brand color) with its own hover/disabled palette, mirroring the existing `.record-sale-btn` pattern. Added a mobile breakpoint rule stacking the three buttons full-width. All new selectors are scoped under `.form-actions`/specific classes rather than bare `.primary-btn`/`.secondary-btn`, so no other page's buttons are affected.
